- Hit ratios are an integral cost driver in insurance agencies. 
- In an insurance agency, hit ratios on new business average 20% to 30%. 
- Average time required to quote a new commercial middle-market account generating a commission of $1,000 to $2,000 is eight hours for CSRs and 10 hours for producers.
- At a 25% hit ratio, the agency spends 15% of all working days on generating zero revenue.

